msContents.summary: Two works copied in two different hands bound together and intermixed. The first contains selections from the Qurʼān and prayers. Some prayers have Ottoman Turkish titles in red. A few leaves inserted upside down (f. 12-15, 18-19). The second text is a set of questions and answers in Ottoman Turkish on faith and religion associated with the name Luṭfī ibn ʻAbd al-Muʻīn (f. 54v). Some notes in Latin script throughout.

msItem.title: Book of prayers and questions and answers
[Book of prayers and questions and answers]

supportDesc.extent: [Turkey?] : 138 x 88 (93 x 52) mm, bound to 144 x 93 x 12 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Text 1 written in 9 long lines; text 2 written in 17 long lines.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Border-rules in gold and black; verses punctuated by gold roundels; some rubrications and overlining in red.

binding.p: Bound in reddish leather with blind tooled frame rules; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Item is not dated; probably late 18th or 19th century.

provenance: Formerly owned by George Arthur Plimpton (bookplate inside front cover).
